         <abstract>
            <p>An iterative algorithm with fast convergence can be used to compute logorithms, inverse circular functions, or inverse hyperbolic functions according to the choice of initial conditions. Only rational operations and square roots are required. The method consists in adding an auxiliary recurrence relation to Borchardt's algorithm to speed the convergence.</p>
          </abstract>
